---
# clang-tidy overrides for host-side unit tests.
# Inherits from the repo-root .clang-tidy and relaxes rules that conflict
# with stub-based test patterns.
#
# - readability-redundant-declaration: tests define stubs for functions
#   declared in firmware headers (e.g. uart_tx_busy). The stub definition
#   precedes the header #include, which clang-tidy flags as redundant.
# - readability-inconsistent-declaration-parameter-name: stubs ignore args
#   via (void)arg and use short local names; parameter names in the header
#   (idx/min_val/max_val) are not observable by the stub.
InheritParentConfig: true

Checks: >
  -readability-redundant-declaration,
  -readability-inconsistent-declaration-parameter-name
...
